{{Otheruses|the Ōtsuka Kofun Cluster located in Ichikawamisato, Yamanashi Prefecture|other similarly named kofun clusters|Ōtsuka Kofun Cluster}} '''Ōtsuka Kofun Cluster''' (大塚古墳群) refers to a group of {{ill|kofun|ja|古墳|1=Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (ancient Kofuns) located in {{ill|Ichikawamisato|ja|市川三郷町|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Nishiyatsushiro District|ja|西八代郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Yamanashi Prefecture|ja|山梨県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
== Overview == The northern part of Ichikawamisato is characterized by the {{ill|Sone Hills|ja|曽根丘陵|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, which feature numerous kofun distributed across the region. These include the {{ill|Kai Chōshizuka Kofun|ja|甲斐銚子塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a keyhole-shaped tumulus from the 4th century located in southern {{ill|Kōfu|ja|甲府市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The Ōtsuka Kofun Cluster contains several keyhole-shaped and round tumuli believed to have spread from the Sone Hills to various parts of the {{ill|Kōfu Basin|ja|甲府盆地|qq=draft|qq=draft}} after the 5th century.
== Details of the Kofun == The cluster includes the following notable kofun:
;Ōtsuka Kofun :A keyhole-shaped kofun ({{ill|scallop-shaped tumulus|ja|帆立貝形古墳|1=Scallop Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) dating back to the mid-Kofun period in the 5th century. ;Emon-zuka Kofun :A keyhole-shaped kofun. ;Isezuka Kofun :A circular kofun. ;Toriibara Kitsunezuka Kofun {{main|{{ill|Toriibara Kitsunezuka Kofun|ja|鳥居原狐塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}}}} :A circular kofun believed to have been constructed around the late 5th century. It is notable for the excavation of a {{ill|dated mirror|ja|紀年銘鏡|qq=draft|qq=draft}} bearing the inscription "May 25, 1st year of Chiwu" (赤烏元年五月二十五日). "Chiwu" (赤烏) was a {{ill|era name|ja|元号|qq=draft|qq=draft}} used during the reign of {{ill|Sun Quan|ja|孫権|qq=draft|qq=draft}} of the {{ill|Wu (Three Kingdoms)|ja|呉 (三国)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, corresponding to 238 CE. This is one of the earliest dated mirrors associated with kofun.
== Related Articles == * {{ill|Sone Hills|ja|曽根丘陵|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
