== Overview == The northern part of Ichikawamisato is characterized by the {{ill|Sone Hill Range|lt=Sone Hill Range|lt=Sone Hills|ja|曽根丘陵|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sone Hills|qq=}}, which feature numerous kofun distributed across the region. These include the [[:en:Kai Chōshizuka Kofun|Kai Chōshizuka Kofun]], a keyhole-shaped tumulus from the 4th century located in southern [[:en:Kōfu|Kōfu]]. The Ōtsuka Kofun Cluster contains several keyhole-shaped and round tumuli believed to have spread from the Sone Hills to various parts of the {{ill|Kōfu Basin|ja|甲府盆地|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōfu Basin|qq=}} after the 5th century.
== Details of the Kofun == The cluster includes the following notable kofun:
;Ōtsuka Kofun :A keyhole-shaped kofun ({{ill|scallop-shaped tumulus|ja|帆立貝形古墳|1=Scallop Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/scallop-shaped tumulus|13=User:Immanuelle/Scallop Kofun|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}}) dating back to the mid-Kofun period in the 5th century. ;Emon-zuka Kofun :A keyhole-shaped kofun. ;Isezuka Kofun :A circular kofun. ;Toriibara Kitsunezuka Kofun {{main|{{ill|Toriibara Kitsunezuka Kofun|ja|鳥居原狐塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toriibara Kitsunezuka Kofun|qq=}}}} :A circular kofun believed to have been constructed around the late 5th century. It is notable for the excavation of a {{ill|dated mirror|ja|紀年銘鏡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/dated mirror|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 紀年銘資料}} bearing the inscription "May 25, 1st year of Chiwu" (赤烏元年五月二十五日). "Chiwu" (赤烏) was a {{ill|era name|ja|元号|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/era name|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} used during the reign of [[:en:Sun Quan|Sun Quan]] of the [[:en:Eastern Wu|Wu (Three Kingdoms)]], corresponding to 238 CE. This is one of the earliest dated mirrors associated with kofun.
